// Project Todos Tools
// Manages project-level todo items stored in a global registry at ~/.mermaid-collab/todos.json.
// Each todo gets an auto-generated session name (adjective-adjective-noun) for use as a vibe session.

Todos are stored globally and filtered by project path at read time.
The session name is generated once at creation and never changes.
A test override (_todosDataDir) redirects the data directory for isolated testing.

FUNCTION generateSessionName() -> string
  Pick two random adjectives and one random noun from the built-in word lists.
  Return them joined as "adj1-adj2-noun".

---

FUNCTION setTodosDataDir(dir) -> void                                            EXPORT
  Override the data directory path (for testing). Pass null to reset to the default.

---

FUNCTION getTodosPath() -> string
  Return the path to todos.json, using the overridden directory if set,
  otherwise ~/.mermaid-collab/todos.json.

---

FUNCTION readTodosFile() -> TodosFile
  Read and parse todos.json. Return empty { todos: [], nextId: 1 } if the file doesn't exist.

---

FUNCTION writeTodosFile(data) -> void
  Ensure the data directory exists. Write todos.json with formatted JSON.

---

FUNCTION listTodos(project) -> ListTodosResult                                   EXPORT
  Read the todos file. Filter todos by the given project path.
  Return { todos: [...], count }.

---

FUNCTION addTodo(project, title) -> AddTodoResult                                EXPORT
  Read todos file. Generate a session name. Build a new todo with auto-incremented ID,
  title, project path, session name, and creation timestamp.
  Append to todos, increment nextId, write file.
  Return { success, todo, count, message }.

---

FUNCTION updateTodo(project, id, updates) -> UpdateTodoResult                    EXPORT
  Read todos file. Find todo by ID and project (return failure if not found).
  Apply title update if provided. Write file.
  Return { success, todo, message }.

---

FUNCTION removeTodo(project, id) -> RemoveTodoResult                             EXPORT
  Read todos file. Find todo by ID and project (return failure if not found).
  Remove it from the array. Write file.
  Return { success, removed, count, message }.
